answerText: viscoelasticity [accept other forms][10] This model for viscoelasticity is modeled by a Newtonian damper and a Hookean elastic spring connected in series. Its namesake also has a set of equations that relate mixed partials of thermodynamic quantities.

question: Question: The storage and loss moduli describe this type of system and are respectively proportional to cosine and sine of the phase difference between stress and strain.  [10] Name this property of a material to exhibit characteristics of both liquids and solids when exposed to different deformation rates.
